    "description": "The House On Holland Hill is a 15-20 minute visual novel, originally made during an Idle Thumbs gamejam. <br><br>You assume the role of Luigi, a zesty food delivery driver, and your first delivery takes you to a newly-built house outside of town. It's an imposingly modern villa, like one you would see on ArchDaily's Instagram account; Smooth angular surfaces, a big driveway, lots of windows to peek into... You have a chat with the charismatic owner, hand over the food, and get on your way. <br><br>Before long, you start to receive more orders from this address. You develop a rapport with the home owners, and over time, you start to get the impression that not all is well behind the front door of The House On Holland Hill. <br><br>Featuring:<br><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li> 3D environment to wander around in<br></li><li> Hand-painted 2D characters to meet<br></li><li> A game length that won't waste your time<br></li><li> 13 deliveries to make<br></li><li> Four possible endings to arrive at<br></li><li> Peep on the lives of the inhabitants of the house<br></li><li> Get involved or remain professional<br></li><li> Find out what's going on behind closed doors<br></li><li> Navigate interactive dialogues<br></li><li> Keyboard and controller support</li></ul>",
